text.tspan: Depressive disorders prevalence vs. GDP per capita, 2019
Estimated share of people who have depressive disorders, whether or not they were diagnosed, based on
representative surveys, medical data and statistical modelling.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019); Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
